					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-751007#post-1918129</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-751007/scp-1567#post-1918129</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 18 Dec 2013 21:28:49 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Musuko</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1406594</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I figure there are two options:</p> <p>1: We have, but it didn't add anything useful to the containment procedures, so it's not detailed here.<br /> 2: We haven't, because we've already got this thing successfully contained, and the need to learn more about it comes secondary to the need to contain it, and since we don't know what -2 or -3 might do as the result of intrusion by air, it might be best to stay out.</p> <p>Edit: after all&#8230;it's an autonomous, possibly sentient, centuries old train that spews out blinding light and lethal levels of radiation&#8230;we really don't want to give it an incentive to start flying.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-751007#post-1918127</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-751007/scp-1567#post-1918127</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 18 Dec 2013 21:24:36 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Musuko</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1406594</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Good catch on the exahertz, thank you. That was a typo. I've corrected it now.</p> <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Spoiler</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Spoiler</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <p>The beast has always been in the form of a 1995 train. Nobody (outside of Gallington at any rate) knows why.</p> </div> </div> </div> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
