					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-751007#post-1918076</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-751007/scp-1567#post-1918076</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 18 Dec 2013 19:46:51 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Michael Atreus</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1343778</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>The photo is marvelously spooky, but I need more hints about how or why the Beast assumed the form of a train to buy into this skip.</p> <p>I think that exaherts should be exahertz, but I notice there's a UK spelling of ionizing used here, so in case that's a legitimate spelling of the SI unit on the other side of the pond, I thought it best to just point it out for review.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-751007#post-1918068</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-751007/scp-1567#post-1918068</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 18 Dec 2013 19:38:29 +0000</pubDate>
								<wikidot:authorUserId>1361261</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I thought about this a little while after reading, and decided to upvote based on the stuff around the edges on this one. I like the little things, such as the software designed to affect radiological equipment as part of containment or the task force researching the design of the locomotive. I also like that you left the details of what exactly is happening in the town largely to the imagination in this case.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
